infodynamics.measures.continuous.kraskov

Class PredictiveInfoCalculatorKraskov

  • java.lang.Object
    • infodynamics.measures.continuous.PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo
      • infodynamics.measures.continuous.kraskov.PredictiveInfoCalculatorKraskov
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PredictiveInfoCalculator

    public class PredictiveInfoCalculatorKraskov
extends PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo
    A Predictive Information (PI) / Excess Entropy calculator (implementing PredictiveInfoCalculator) which is affected using a Kraskov-Stoegbauer-Grassberger (KSG) Mutual Information (MI) calculator (MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskov) to make the calculations.

    That is, this class implements a PI calculator using the KSG nearest-neighbour approach. This is achieved by plugging in MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskov as the calculator into the parent class PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo.

    Usage is as per the paradigm outlined for PredictiveInfoCalculator, with:

    • The constructor step is either a simple call to PredictiveInfoCalculatorKraskov(), or else specifies which KSG algorithm to implement via PredictiveInfoCalculatorKraskov(int) or PredictiveInfoCalculatorKraskov(String);
    • PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo.setProperty(String, String) allowing properties for MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKraskov.setProperty(String, String) (except MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariate.PROP_TIME_DIFF as outlined in PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo.setProperty(String, String)).
    • Computed values are in nats, not bits!

    References:

    • Bialek, W., Nemenman, I., and Tishby, N., "Complexity through nonextensivity", Physica A, 302, 89-99. (2001).
    • J. P. Crutchfield, D. P. Feldman, "Regularities Unseen, Randomness Observed: Levels of Entropy Convergence", Chaos, Vol. 13, No. 1. (2003), pp. 25-54.
    Author:
    Joseph Lizier (email, www)
